The AAVA 2.0 metadata represents a significant structural evolution from AAVA 1.0 while preserving core semantic meaning. The workflow definition has been restructured with enhanced agent metadata and improved model deployment specifications. However, this introduces moderate compatibility concerns and requires careful migration planning.
Core workflow concept 'DI_DataSpecs_Modelupdates_SN' preserved across both versions with identical business purpose and agent functionality descriptions.
All three agents (Technical Specification, Delta Model Changes, Functional Test Cases) maintain identical task descriptions and business logic requirements.

Agent descriptions in both versions are identical but extremely verbose (1000+ characters), suggesting need for summary fields in future versions.
AAVA 2.0 represents a minor version evolution with backward-incompatible structural changes requiring migration scripts.
